  "market_context": "Heating oil (USD-denominated) daily chart, June–September 2022. The monthly time frame printed a candle two closure after taking out a prior range high, then closing lower, signalling bearish continuation into the next month.",
  "key_observation": "A monthly candle two closure with range high swept and candle three closing low projects multi-day downside continuation, with intraweek reversals creating fresh swing points for additional continuation entries.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify on the monthly that a range high has been taken out followed by a candle two closure, with candle three closing low — bearish continuation context.",
    "Step 2: Anticipate Monday to expand lower as long as price respects 50% of the prior monthly candle.",
    "Step 3: Monday opens and expands lower as candle four; recognize a new phase of price could form, so avoid chasing and wait for a new swing point.",
    "Step 4: Equal lows form intraday — wait an additional day for a clean swing point rather than entering immediately.",
    "Step 5: Wednesday forms a swing point (intraweek reversal); use 50% of its wick as the point of interest with confluence of equal lows and previous month lows below.",
    "Step 6: Look for Thursday to deliver a continuation lower from that POI; price respects the area and closes below the up-close candle and the equal lows.",
    "Step 7: Given Thursday closes strongly toward the prior lows, anticipate Friday continuation, which delivers and takes out the lows."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation played out as anticipated — Thursday respected the POI and closed below the equal lows, and Friday extended lower to take out the previous lows.",
  "lessons": "After a higher time frame candle two closure, expect multi-day continuation but skip days that have already expanded; wait for a fresh swing point (often an intraweek reversal) with confluence before taking the next continuation entry.",
